rlVizLib.dynamicLoading
Class LocalJarAgentEnvironmentLoader

java.lang.Object
  rlVizLib.dynamicLoading.LocalJarAgentEnvironmentLoader
All Implemented Interfaces:
DynamicLoaderInterface
public class LocalJarAgentEnvironmentLoader
extends java.lang.Object
implements DynamicLoaderInterface

My belief is that our classes are leaking like crazy because we are forever loading them using new classloaders and a bunch of the statically allocated stuff is just hanging around. I want to cache loaded classes so we only load them a single time.

Author:
btanner

loadFromClass

private java.lang.Object loadFromClass(java.lang.Class<?> theClass,
                                       ParameterHolder theParams)
Creates an object of type theClass using theParams if possible. Also checks to see if the version of RLVizLib that was used to compile theClass is the same as the current runtime version. For now, doesn't do anything except print a warning if they don't match.

Parameters:
theClass - Class to instantiate
theParams - ParameterHolder to initialize the new object with
Returns:
newly instantiated class of type theClass
